captions.text: Flores is a laid back island
Although there isn’t much big city on flores
I’m afraid I’m not in flores
Man! I think I’m ended up in aceh
When turbulence hits us, it seems I pray way to long and skipped cities
But that’s fine..i can still take naya to the edge of Indonesia
This is not the edge of Indonesia..dumbass!
At least I can still take her to aceh
Because right now I’m in aceh
I have to adapt to it’s local custom
Have you ever been to aceh?
This is my first time in aceh
What do we do? I’m not familiar with the place
Well that’s okay.. who knows while traveling we stumbled upon a random treasures
Best way to understand the place is by looking for the local folks
How do we say jalan jalan man in aceh?
There are no means and strength except from Allah
Truly we are inferior to God
My first impression about aceh it’s awesome in spiritual kind of way
Look at the signs..it fills with positive things
And the most important thing..never give up
In aceh we have to be more polite
Because aceh is a very religious
We’re in rumah makan aceh rayeuk
according to travel show on the tv
in order to understand the local custom we had to eat what they eat
because you are what you eat
if I ate humans.. then I became human too?
Then that means I was fed humans when I was a kid!?
Anyways… even though aceh’s cuisine has a similarity with other Sumatran
Aceh rayeuk was infamous..and they open several branches as well…
Ayam tangkep is one of their special
Cos they had to catch them while we’re waiting for the meal
It’s more like the chicken were covered with the leaves
In here we called it temuru
When we picked the chicken, it’s concealed within the leaves..
Because it’s hidden we’re gonna catch it!
After we had our meal we looked around and I realized that the architecture was a mixed between futuristic and serambi makkah
Woow! this is the masjid baiturahman!
Even though the outsides are very hot..for some reason it stays cool inside
It’s hot on the outside..cool on the inside
Personally the best thing in here (inaudible)
What’s the most memorable things in aceh?
In here.. it was the religion
They really hold dear to their faith
There’s a sparrow inside the mosque
Alright.. do you have a camera?
Alright! I got the pre-wed pictures
There’s this one thing about aceh that’s really stuck one me
Wherever you turn your head, you can see what’s tsunami left of
Of which they were turned nowadays as a tourist spot
Like a boat that stuck on top of the roof
God always works on a mysterious ways
Because sometimes not every moment we were having good times
On the other hand, there’s a meaning behind all of this
Now we’re going inside the boat that sits on top of the house
So when we’re in the middle of the road, we came across a river of which there were many fisherman’s boats
This here were also one of them
It’s being swept across this lampulo housing area
Although this is a housing area
It was like crashing the house and the booom! And stuck here
I asked locals that when the event takes place there wasn’t any single soul on the boat
And then people evacuate into this boat
The disaster brought significant changes to aceh
How can it not? See it for yourself
There was a bridge and now it’s gone
There was houses and now there’s none
Because of tsunami there’s was a new whole kinds of flowers in the area
And the flower gave a wonderful scent
Aceh’s local made an awesome museum
I’m sure that there will be…
There will be something that will make my heart moved
I’m sure whomever built this museum is a genius!
Every room has it’s own symbols
It was like a stage house..
and they made it elevated so people can evacuate in case there’s a tsunami
The carving on the wall represents saman dance
A dance which symbolizes teamwork between humans
If you ever went to this museum you will see many awesome things
It’s a tunnel which shows us how does it feels trapped inside the big waves
Can you feel like it’s a rain drops?
And then there’s a chamber where it was dedicated for the victim of tsunami
Of which if you looked up you will see…
God always look out for his people
This is the name of the victim right?
Very touching to the point where we were in the dark tunnel
We saw light at the end of it and then we see the whole world
This symbolizes where the whole world stretching out their hands to help us
What do you want to see?
This one..i really wanted to see it
Because it was like everything around it was reduced to nothing
And yet there’s only one mosque that was still standing
I really wanted to pray there
We’re on the rooftop of the museum
There has to be Allah’s symbol
Yet exciting in kind of way
It’s more like a touching moments mixed with this uneasy feelings because of the disaster that befalls aceh
There’s a lot of sorrows and despairs..
but there’s always a meaning behind all of this
God helps us by showing us the whole world reaching out to us
It was like when we’re in despair..
This is how tsunami made the locals to become more strong
I wonder how they are right now
Are they still mourn over this?
Or they have moved on and contribute more to rebuilding it?
But more importantly I gotta finish my song
Now we’re on the main park of which I forgot the name of it
There’s spiderman… transformers… Scooby doo… doraemon!
To be honest I thought aceh was strict
You can see that these are the marks which they hold dear
We’re on the Indonesian air force one monument
It is say that locals chipped in to make this so soekarno can travel
And to commemorate those day, they like to do break dance underneath it
I bet you didn’t know they can do this
It’s okay bro… I also just know it now
Where’s my team? come help me!
To close the day, I’m gonna took naya to a beautiful place
Jebraw said that he wanted to brought me to the place where tsunami hits first
It can’t be.. does jebraw wanted to brought me to that mosque?
I wanted to take naya to a cool place
I’m a cool guy you know
I’m sure she would be happy
I have to cherish this.. he took me to this cool place
But occasionally a treasure doesn’t have to be beautiful
This is the prove the divine of God
There has to be 30 meters waves when tsunami hits
Despite that, the mosque holds it’s ground while the others crumbled
Like it was there’s nothing except this building from that before.. and yet there was in fact other too
Even when tsunami hits, they still stand strong
God is good all the time.. and all the time God is good
Look at this.. the water was reaching all the way to the top
That seems to be in poor state
Actually this mosque was quite close with the beach last night
But when we arrived at the beach it’s already dark
So it’s impossible to see it
Awesome.. i’m very happy that I can make naya happy
Thank you jebraw.. for taking me.. to.. lampu’uk mosque
Eventhough we didn’t make it to the edge of Indonesia
Every girl having this kind of friend would be very lucky
